  <section class="step" id="understanding">
    <div class="container step-info" >
      <span class="step-number">1</span>
      <h3 class="step-title">Understanding.</h3>
      <p class="step-description">Starting from a clear beginning, we let the whole team to clarify any doubts about the problem, customer, business, users, value proposition, and how successfully the solution could be.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="step" id="definition">
    <div class="container step-info" >
      <span class="step-number">2</span>
      <h3 class="step-title">Definition.</h3>
      <p class="step-description">A scoping session happens with all stakeholders to define the most important elements about the product we are going to build. Having a clear scope is important to build success.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="step" id="design">
    <div class="container step-info" >
      <span class="step-number">3</span>
      <h3 class="step-title">Design.</h3>
      <p class="step-description">The goal is to have a non-functional prototype as fast as possible to see interaction and move forward into coding. The gap between learning and launching a product is huge. This step helps to validate, understand a prove many assumptions earlier in the process of product building.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="step" id="build">
    <div class="container step-info" >
      <span class="step-number">4</span>
      <h3 class="step-title">Build.</h3>
      <p class="step-description">This is when the product becomes alive. Taking the main sprint scope we focus on delivering a functional product in a real environmet so we can involve customers and users the soonest in order to learn, save time and reduce different type of risks.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="step" id="measure">
    <div class="container step-info" >
      <span class="step-number">5</span>
      <h3 class="step-title">Measure.</h3>
      <p class="step-description">Once we involve users and customers into a digital product, things need to be open to change. We use the best tools and techniques to measure engagement and prioritize the next development phases.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
